{"id": 194, "date": "1987-02-23T11:00:33", "date_gmt": "1987-02-23T19:00:33", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=194"}, "modified": "2026-06-09T10:20:29", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-09T17:20:29", "slug": "meeting-across-the-river-bruce-springsteen-and-rosanne-cash", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/02/23/meeting-across-the-river-bruce-springsteen-and-rosanne-cash/", "title": {"rendered": "Sea of Heartbreak"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>&#8220;Sea of Heartbreak&#8221; first became a hit in 1961, when Don Gibson took it all the way to #2 on the Billboard Hot Country Singles chart.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/A4bo4ByFhLM?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>It charted again eleven years later, when Kenny Price took it to #24.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/PDplFSIA0Bw?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8230;and again in 1989, when Ronnie McDowell took it to #39, marking three consecutive decades for with Top 40 country status for &#8220;Sea of Heartbreak.&#8221;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/aCyZStpJzXY?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>If only Johnny Cash had released it as a single when he recorded it for his 1996\u00a0<em>Unchained\u00a0</em>album, &#8220;Sea of Heartbreak&#8221; might have charted for <em>four</em> consecutive decades.</p>\n<p>He didn&#8217;t though, and the streak ended. But that didn&#8217;t stop Cash&#8217;s daughter Rosanne from taking a run at it herself in 2009.</p>\n<p>Well, not exactly by herself.\u00a0From Cash&#8217;s album, <em>The List, </em>here&#8217;s &#8220;Sea of Heartbreak&#8221; with Bruce Springsteen.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/A3LSrcKksCo?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Rosanne and Bruce performed &#8220;Sea of Heartbreak&#8221; together just once, at Rosanne&#8217;s show in Durham, North Carolina in 2010. No recording circulates from that performance.</p>\n<p><strong>Sea of Heartbreak<br />\nRecorded:</strong> ?<br />\n<strong>Released:\u00a0</strong><em>The List</em> (2009)<br />\n<strong>First performed:</strong> April 15, 2010 (Durham, NC)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> April 15, 2010 (Durham, NC)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 January 12, 2018</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>&#8220;Sea of Heartbreak&#8221; first became a hit in 1961, when Don Gibson took it all the way to #2 on the Billboard Hot Country Singles&hellip;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69775, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_feature_clip_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false}, "categories": [3617, 5], "tags": [2981, 280, 77, 78], "class_list": ["post-194", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-it-takes-two", "category-meeting-across-the-river", "tag-don-gibson", "tag-johnny-cash", "tag-rosanne-cash", "tag-sea-of-heartbreak"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/ab67616d0000b273e92d3bbdc1399ca0a7aaf47c.jpg?fit=1280%2C1280&ssl=1", "jetpack_sharing_enabled": true, "jetpack_shortlink": "https://wp.me/p9w3Lk-38", "jetpack_likes_enabled": true, "jetpack-related-posts": [{"id": 11632, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com